# The clean fix (minimal changes)

Wrap the **CFT notify + move logic** in a `try/catch` and move the failed file to `/failed`.

### Change this part of your code

Current:

```java
cftApiClient.notifyAndWaitForCompletion(key, encryptedFileName, maxWait);

addProcessedKey(stepExecution, encryptedFileName);

if (moveEnabled) {
    moveToProcessed(encryptedFileName, key);
}
```

---

### Replace with

```java
try {

    cftApiClient.notifyAndWaitForCompletion(key, encryptedFileName, maxWait);

    addProcessedKey(stepExecution, encryptedFileName);

    if (moveEnabled) {
        moveToProcessed(encryptedFileName, key);
    }

} catch (Exception ex) {

    log.error("CFT transfer failed for file {}", encryptedFileName, ex);

    moveToFailed(encryptedFileName, key);

}
```

---

# Add a new helper

```java
private void moveToFailed(String encryptedFileName, String key) {

    try {

        String failedKey = "failed/" + encryptedFileName;

        cosStorageService.moveFile(key, failedKey);

        log.info("Moved outgoing COS file {} to failed location {}", key, failedKey);

    } catch (Exception e) {

        log.warn("Failed moving {} to failed location: {}", key, e.getMessage());

    }

}
```

---

# Why this works

Your loop in `findTargetAndPgpUpload()` continues:

```
Miles → processed
Finance → timeout → moved to failed
Loop continues
```

No file is lost.

